items.title: Q2 results: Nifty companies show zero profit growth leading to downgrades
items.description: September quarter results reveal weaker-than-expected earnings, with a flat YoY growth for 34 Nifty companies. Key downgrades in earnings estimates affected FY25 and FY26 projections, led by BPCL, Reliance Industries, and Coal India. Mixed performance noted across banks, IT, consumer, and oil marketing companies.

items.title: Q2 results today: IRFC, IRCTC, Raymond among 47 companies to announce earnings on Monday
items.description: Key companies, including IRFC, IRCTC, and Raymond, are set to announce their quarterly earnings today. Amara Raja Energy is anticipated to report a 17% YoY growth in net profit and a 10% YoY increase in revenue, driven by solid performance in the aftermarket division and new energy business.
